Starting from August 7, 2020 until November 8, 2020, the government of Lithuania announced that higher education and continuing vocational training is recommended to be provided remotely. The necessary conditions for public health safety, hygiene, provision of persons with necessary personal protective equipment must be ensured: disinfection; 
hand hygiene (washing and/or disinfection); 
prohibition to work for employees with symptoms or if isolation is prescribed;

Starting from August 7, 2020, until November 8, 2020, the Government of Lithuania announced that 5– 12 grade pupils will learn remotely except for children educated in special institutions and special classes in general education schools. The necessary conditions for public health safety, hygiene, provision of persons with necessary personal protective equipment must be ensured: disinfection; 
hand hygiene (washing and/or disinfection); 
prohibition to work for employees with symptoms or if isolation is prescribed.

As of July 1, 2021, Lithuanian citizens may be vaccinated in Lithuania against Covid-19, regardless of their place or country of residence, as well as other persons who:

- are entitled to personal health care services paid from the Compulsory Health Insurance Fund or from the State budget;
- citizens of the Member States of the European Union and the European Free Trade Association and their family members, who have come to live in Lithuania for the period exceeding 3 months in 6 months, and who have been granted the right to reside in Lithuania;
- foreign citizens and persons without citizenship, to whom the Lithuanian residence permit has been issued;
- persons accredited and residing in Lithuania;
other persons who have to be vaccinated by the Government’s resolution.

As of August 7, 2020, Lithuania's government published COVID-19 restriction guidelines for catering establishments and private sector which include working hours, social distance, mask policy, and hygiene requirements: Remote work recommended;
Services and trade and activities at leisure and entertainment venues: distance in queues is at least 1 meter; disinfection and hygiene requirements; no working with symptoms or if isolation is prescribed;  
leisure and entertainment venues: mandatory registration of visitors (given name, surname and telephone number);
In Raseiniai district municipality - remote working, except when the relevant functions must be performed only at the workplace. This requirement is recommended for the private sector too.  
At least 10 sq. m. of space per person and 2 metre distance in cultural, leisure, entertainment and sports establishments.

